        "b1": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "The making process, step by step",
            "text": "<ul><li><strong>Design & proof:</strong> shape, finish and engraving layout, approved digitally first.</li><li><strong>Material shaping:</strong> crystal and acrylic are precision-cut; metal is cast or pressed; wood is machined.</li><li><strong>Engraving & printing:</strong> laser engraving (incl. sub-surface 3D in crystal) and full-colour UV printing.</li><li><strong>Plating & polishing:</strong> electroplated finishes on metal; edge polishing on crystal/glass.</li><li><strong>Assembly & QC:</strong> bases, name plates and a final quality check.</li><li><strong>Packing & dispatch:</strong> foam-cradled, double-boxed and tracked.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "b2": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Why in-house matters",
            "text": "<p>Because we run design, engraving, printing, plating and QC <strong>under one roof in Bangalore</strong>, quality stays consistent and timelines are reliable even at bulk volumes — unlike resellers who depend on third parties. (See <a href=\"/pages/best-trophy-manufacturers-india-2026\">how to choose a manufacturer</a>.)</p>"
          }
        },
        "b3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How are crystal trophies engraved?",
            "answer": "<p>With lasers — surface 2D etching and sub-surface 3D engraving that places a logo inside the crystal.</p>"
          }
